INVESTING IN OUR PEOPLE 






BenefitsTrainingWomen's InitiativeEvents



We provide best-in-class benefits for all of our employees in a unique, fun and collaborative work environment. Some of our benefits include:

 




Excellent medical, dental, and vision plans for you and your family
401(k) retirement plan with annual company contribution
A comprehensive Wellness Program
State-of-the-art office spaces
Commuter benefits program








 Fully paid parental leave  Weekly catered breakfast series and fully-stocked pantries  Specialty gifts for extraordinary contributors  Generous paid time off  Work/life balance and firm-sponsored social events







Find out what being part of our family means for your family. Read more about our Parental Benefits or View Our Brochure






We invest in our talent. We offer our people opportunities for cultivating their knowledge and skills through training programs such as:

 













Executive Communication Skills These programs expand the verbal and written range of even our most experienced communicators. Management Training We train new and experienced managers on the art and science of managing teams, teaching skills like delegation, providing feedback, and dealing with sensitive issues. Credit Derivatives Workshop This workshop is offered at varying skill levels to provide an overview of credit and structured credit products and how these fit into our firm’s market strategies. Financial Engineering This in-depth module focuses on modeling, pricing and risk management.









We believe that diversity – of both people and thought – results in the best outcomes for our employees and our clients. We’re committed to ensuring that our women employees can thrive at BlueMountain. We’ve created a Women’s Network to help centralize our efforts in this regard, including:

 













Industry Networking

“100 Women in Hedge Funds” Education Sessions
Deutsche Bank’s “Women on Wall Street Conference”

Professional Development Educational sessions, including: ‘Negotiation Conditions for Leadership Success’, ‘Beyond the Corporate Ladder: New Career Paradigms for Changing Times’, and ‘Personal Style, Professional Impact.’ Social
Annual global Women’s Event with a prominent keynote speaker, casual social events and happy hours.
Volunteer Hot Bread’s Kitchen Volunteer Event, Dress for Success









We believe that relationships are shaped both inside and outside the office. We promote social events and extracurricular activities throughout the year.









